-- NBC loses dealmaking executive to Discovery
-- 
-- Thu Mar 15, 2007 6:14pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/15/us-discovery-executive-idUSN1516284920070315

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - NBC Universal lost another key executive on Thursday when Discovery Communications Inc. announced it hired Bruce Campbell as president of its digital media business and business development. 


 Campbell, who is currently executive vice president of business development for NBC Universal, will start his new job next month, closely held Discovery Communications said. In the role, Campbell will oversee acquisitions, joint ventures and all major business transactions for Discovery Communications, which runs the Discovery Channel and The Science Channel, among other properties. Campbell will report to Chief Executive David Zaslav, another former NBC Universal executive. As a key dealmaker for NBC Universal, Campbell played a role the acquisitions of Telemundo, Vivendi Universal Entertainment and iVillage. NBC Universal, meanwhile, is undergoing a management shift, with Jeff Zucker having taken over as CEO from Bob Wright. Another key executive, Randy Falco, left NBC Universal to become CEO of Time Warner Inc's ( TWX.N ) AOL last year. NBC Universal is 80 percent owned by blue-chip conglomerate General Electric Co. ( GE.N ) and 20 percent owned by France's Vivendi ( VIV.PA ).